PURPOSE
-------
This document catalogs default ports, URI paths, request/response formats, and
fingerprinting characteristics for the most widely deployed self-hosted LLM
inference frameworks. This is the authoritative reference for configuring a
honeypot that mimics exposed LLM infrastructure and captures scanner/attacker
prompt payloads.

Threat context: Cisco Talos (Sep 2025) identified 1,100+ exposed Ollama instances
via Shodan in under 10 minutes. Censys found ~10,600 high-confidence exposed
Ollama instances globally. Pillar Security (Jan 2026) documented "Operation
Bizarre Bazaar" — a commercial LLMjacking supply chain averaging 972 attacks/day
against exposed LLM endpoints, with a 2–8 hour lag between public scan indexing
and active exploitation. Threat actors use Shodan and Censys to find you; once
listed, probing begins within hours.

