SECTION 1: FRAMEWORK ENDPOINT REFERENCE
================================================================================

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
1.1 OLLAMA
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Default Port:       11434 (TCP)
Alternate Ports:    11435, 11439 (obscurity attempts); 80, 443, 8080 (behind proxy)
Bind Default:       127.0.0.1 (changed to 0.0.0.0 via OLLAMA_HOST env var to expose)
HTTP Server:        Uvicorn (ASGI)

Banner Fingerprints:
  - HTTP Header: "Server: uvicorn" or contains "Ollama"
  - Root endpoint: GET / returns "Ollama is running" (plain text, 200)

Key API Endpoints (native Ollama API):
  GET  /                          -> "Ollama is running" (liveness probe)
  GET  /api/tags                  -> list available models (JSON)
  GET  /api/version               -> version info
  POST /api/generate              -> single-turn completion (stream or batch)
  POST /api/chat                  -> multi-turn chat completion
  POST /api/embed                 -> generate embeddings
  POST /api/pull                  -> pull a model (attacker pivot: unauthorized upload)
  POST /api/push                  -> push a model
  POST /api/create                -> create a model from Modelfile
  DELETE /api/delete              -> delete a model
  POST /api/copy                  -> copy a model
  GET  /api/ps                    -> list currently running models

OpenAI-Compatible Endpoints (88.9% of exposed instances use these per Cisco Talos):
  POST /v1/chat/completions       -> OpenAI-style chat
  POST /v1/completions            -> OpenAI-style completion
  POST /v1/embeddings             -> OpenAI-style embeddings
  GET  /v1/models                 -> list models

Sample /api/generate request body:
  { "model": "llama2", "prompt": "...", "stream": false }

Sample /v1/chat/completions request body:
  { "model": "llama2", "messages": [{"role":"user","content":"..."}] }

Honeypot Notes:
  - Most scanners hit /api/tags first to enumerate models, then /api/generate or
    /v1/chat/completions with the probe prompt.
  - Root GET is a common liveness check. Always return "Ollama is running" (200).
  - Model /api/tags response should list plausible models:
    llama2, llama3, mistral, codellama, gemma, phi3, qwen2, deepseek-r1

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
1.2 VLLM
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Default Port:       8000 (TCP)
HTTP Server:        Uvicorn (FastAPI backend)
Auth:               None by default

Key API Endpoints (OpenAI-compatible):
  GET  /health                    -> {"status":"healthy"} — liveness probe
  GET  /v1/models                 -> model list
  POST /v1/chat/completions       -> chat inference
  POST /v1/completions            -> text completion
  POST /v1/embeddings             -> embeddings
  GET  /metrics                   -> Prometheus metrics (reveals system info)
  GET  /docs                      -> Swagger/OpenAPI UI (FastAPI default)
  GET  /openapi.json              -> OpenAPI schema

Banner Fingerprints:
  - HTTP Header: "Server: uvicorn"
  - /docs page title contains "vLLM"
  - /openapi.json info.title = "vLLM"

Honeypot Notes:
  - /health and /v1/models are common first-touch probes.
  - /metrics is a goldmine for attackers (reveals GPU count, VRAM, model loaded).
    Return plausible but fake Prometheus metrics.
  - Swagger at /docs is a distinctive fingerprint — include it.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
1.3 LOCALAI
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Default Port:       8080 (TCP)
HTTP Server:        Go-based HTTP server
Auth:               Optional API key (often absent)

Key API Endpoints (OpenAI-compatible + extras):
  GET  /                          -> "LocalAI" landing or 200 OK
  GET  /v1/models                 -> model list
  POST /v1/chat/completions       -> chat inference
  POST /v1/completions            -> text completion
  POST /v1/embeddings             -> embeddings
  POST /v1/images/generations     -> image generation (Stable Diffusion backend)
  POST /v1/audio/transcriptions   -> Whisper transcription
  POST /v1/audio/speech           -> TTS
  GET  /readyz                    -> readiness probe
  GET  /healthz                   -> health probe

Distinctive Endpoints (not in OpenAI):
  GET  /v1/backends               -> list available inference backends
  POST /v1/stores/set             -> key-value store
  GET  /v1/stores/get             -> key-value retrieval

Banner Fingerprints:
  - Responds to /readyz and /healthz (Kubernetes health probe pattern)
  - /v1/backends is unique to LocalAI
  - Server header often blank or "local-ai"

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
1.4 LITELLM PROXY
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Default Port:       4000 (TCP) — primary
Alternate Port:     8000 (TCP) — older docs
HTTP Server:        FastAPI / Uvicorn

Key API Endpoints:
  GET  /health                    -> {"status":"healthy","litellm_status":"ok",...}
  GET  /v1/models                 -> model list with provider info
  POST /v1/chat/completions       -> proxied chat completion
  POST /v1/completions            -> proxied text completion
  POST /v1/embeddings             -> proxied embeddings
  GET  /model/info                -> detailed model configuration
  GET  /model/metrics             -> usage metrics per model
  POST /key/generate              -> generate API key (admin endpoint)
  POST /key/delete                -> delete API key
  GET  /spend/logs                -> spend/usage logs (very sensitive)
  GET  /user/info                 -> user info
  POST /team/new                  -> create team
  GET  /global/spend              -> global cost tracking
  GET  /docs                      -> FastAPI Swagger UI
  GET  /utils/transform_request   -> debug: shows how request is transformed

Banner Fingerprints:
  - /docs Swagger title = "LiteLLM API"
  - /health returns litellm_status field
  - Port 4000 is highly distinctive

Honeypot Notes:
  - Admin endpoints (/key/generate, /spend/logs, /global/spend) are high-value
    targets for attackers probing for credential theft or cost hijacking.
  - Return fake spend logs with plausible provider names and dollar amounts.

