1.7 LM STUDIO (lmstudio-server / llmster daemon)
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Default Port:       1234 (TCP)
HTTP Server:        Custom Node.js server (lmstudio SDK)

Key API Endpoints (OpenAI-compatible via /v1 prefix):
  GET  /v1/models                 -> list loaded models
  POST /v1/chat/completions       -> chat inference
  POST /v1/completions            -> text completion
  POST /v1/embeddings             -> embeddings
  GET  /                          -> may return 200 or redirect

Banner Fingerprints:
  - Port 1234 is fairly distinctive
  - No explicit server header (custom stack)
  - /v1 prefix required; bare /chat/completions will 404

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
1.8 LLAMA.CPP SERVER (llama-server)
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Default Port:       8080 (TCP)
HTTP Server:        C++ built-in HTTP server (llama.cpp)
Auth:               None by default

Key API Endpoints:
  GET  /health                    -> {"status":"ok"} or {"status":"loading model"}
  POST /completion                -> text completion (native format, no /v1 prefix)
  POST /v1/chat/completions       -> OpenAI-compat chat
  POST /v1/completions            -> OpenAI-compat text
  GET  /v1/models                 -> model list
  POST /tokenize                  -> tokenize input text
  POST /detokenize                -> detokenize tokens
  GET  /props                     -> server properties (model name, context size, etc.)
  GET  /slots                     -> active inference slots
  GET  /metrics                   -> Prometheus metrics
  GET  /                          -> Swagger-like HTML UI

Banner Fingerprints:
  - /completion (no /v1 prefix) is unique to llama.cpp native API
  - /props returns model metadata including model file path (path disclosure)
  - /slots is unique to llama.cpp

Honeypot Notes:
  - /props is extremely attractive to attackers — reveals model file path on disk,
    context size, n_threads, n_gpu_layers. Return convincing fake data.
  - /slots shows parallel inference context — return a plausible idle slot.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
1.9 OPEN WEBUI (formerly Ollama WebUI)
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Default Port:       3000 (TCP) or 8080 (Docker)
HTTP Server:        SvelteKit / Node.js frontend; Python FastAPI backend

Key API Endpoints:
  GET  /                          -> web application HTML
  GET  /api/config                -> server configuration
  POST /api/chat                  -> proxied chat (internal)
  GET  /api/models                -> available models
  POST /ollama/api/generate       -> proxied Ollama native
  POST /ollama/api/chat           -> proxied Ollama native
  POST /openai/v1/chat/completions -> proxied OpenAI-compat

Banner Fingerprints:
  - HTML title contains "Open WebUI"
  - /api/config returns Open WebUI configuration JSON

