SECTION 4: HONEYPOT RESPONSE STRATEGY
================================================================================

GOAL: Appear to be a real, unauthenticated Ollama/vLLM instance. Accept any
request, return plausible 200 responses, log everything.

RECOMMENDED PERSONA: Ollama (most common, most fingerprinted, scanners know it)

Response headers to include:
  Content-Type: application/json
  Server: uvicorn             <- critical fingerprint
  X-Request-Id: <random uuid>

/api/tags response (GET, 200):
  {
    "models": [
      {"name":"llama3:8b","modified_at":"2025-12-01T00:00:00Z","size":4661234567,
       "digest":"sha256:abc123...","details":{"format":"gguf","family":"llama",
       "parameter_size":"8B","quantization_level":"Q4_0"}},
      {"name":"mistral:7b","modified_at":"2025-11-15T00:00:00Z","size":4109000000,
       "digest":"sha256:def456...","details":{"format":"gguf","family":"mistral",
       "parameter_size":"7B","quantization_level":"Q4_K_M"}},
      {"name":"deepseek-r1:7b","modified_at":"2026-01-10T00:00:00Z","size":4200000000,
       "digest":"sha256:ghi789...","details":{"format":"gguf","family":"deepseek",
       "parameter_size":"7B","quantization_level":"Q4_K_M"}}
    ]
  }

/v1/chat/completions and /api/generate response:
  - Return a plausible but innocuous assistant response
  - Include model name, usage token counts, finish_reason, etc.
  - Do NOT return the attacker's prompt back to them verbatim
  - Inject subtle delay (1-3 seconds) to simulate real inference

GET / response:
  Body: "Ollama is running"
  Status: 200

Key capture fields to log per request:
  - Timestamp (UTC ISO)
  - Source IP + Source Port
  - User-Agent header
  - Authorization header (attacker API key attempts)
  - X-API-Key header
  - Full request URI
  - HTTP method
  - Full request body (JSON payload — THIS IS THE PAYLOAD OF INTEREST)
  - Content-Length
  - Full request headers

